==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[recrudescere]]'' "to become raw again"; from ''[[re-]]'' + ''[[crudescere]]'' "to become hard or raw"

=== Adjective ===
'''recrudescent'''
# breaking out again or [[reemerging]] after temporary [[abatement]] or [[supression]]
#: ''This seems to be a [[recrudescent]] strain of the plague rather than a new desease altogether.''
# (''archaic'') growing [[raw]], [[sore]], or [[painful]] again